    "content": "<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n    <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n    <title>Visual Binary Search Tree</title>\n    <style>\n        @import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Playfair+Display:wght@400;700&family=Montserrat:wght@300;400;600&display=swap');\n\n        :root {\n            --primary: #2c3e50;\n            --secondary: #3498db;\n            --accent: #e74c3c;\n            --light: #ecf0f1;\n            --dark: #2c3e50;\n            --text: #34495e;\n            --background: #f9f9f9;\n            --node-bg: #ffffff;\n            --shadow: 0 10px 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);\n        }\n\n        body {\n            font-family: 'Montserrat', sans-serif;\n            background-color: var(--background);\n            color: var(--text);\n            margin: 0;\n            padding: 0;\n            display: flex;\n            flex-direction: column;\n            align-items: center;\n            min-height: 100vh;\n            overflow-x: hidden;\n        }\n\n        header {\n            width: 100%;\n            padding: 2rem 0;\n            text-align: center;\n            background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--primary), var(--dark));\n            color: white;\n            box-shadow: var(--shadow);\n            margin-bottom: 3rem;\n        }\n\n        h1 {\n            font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;\n            font-size: 2.8rem;\n            margin: 0;\n            letter-spacing: 1px;\n        }\n\n        h2 {\n            font-weight: 300;\n            font-size: 1.2rem;\n            margin: 0.5rem 0 0;\n            opacity: 0.9;\n        }\n\n        .container {\n            width: 90%;\n            max-width: 1200px;\n            display: flex;\n            flex-direction: column;\n            align-items: center;\n        }\n\n        .controls {\n            display: flex;\n            gap: 1rem;\n            margin-bottom: 2rem;\n        }\n\n        button {\n            background-color: var(--secondary);\n            color: white;\n            border: none;\n            padding: 0.8rem 1.5rem;\n            font-family: 'Montserrat', sans-serif;\n            font-size: 1rem;\n            border-radius: 4px;\n            cursor: pointer;\n            transition: all 0.3s ease;\n            box-shadow: 0 4px 6px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);\n        }\n\n        button:hover {\n            background-color: var(--accent);\n            transform: translateY(-2px);\n            box-shadow: 0 6px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.15);\n        }\n\n        .tree-container {\n            width: 100%;\n            min-height: 500px;\n            position: relative;\n            margin: 2rem 0;\n            overflow: hidden;\n            background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.8);\n            border-radius: 12px;\n            padding: 2rem;\n            box-shadow: var(--shadow);\n        }\n\n        .node {\n            position: absolute;\n            width: 60px;\n            height: 60px;\n            border-radius: 50%;\n            background-color: var(--node-bg);\n            display: flex;\n            align-items: center;\n            justify-content: center;\n            font-weight: 600;\n            font-size: 1.2rem;\n            color: var(--primary);\n            box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);\n            transition: all 0.5s ease;\n            z-index: 2;\n            border: 3px solid var(--secondary);\n        }\n\n        .node.highlight {\n            background-color: var(--accent);\n            color: white;\n            transform: scale(1.1);\n            box-shadow: 0 0 20px rgba(231, 76, 60, 0.6);\n        }\n\n        .edge {\n            position: absolute;\n            height: 3px;\n            background-color: var(--secondary);\n            transform-origin: 0 0;\n            z-index: 1;\n            transition: all 0.5s ease;\n        }\n\n        .info-panel {\n            background-color: white;\n            border-radius: 8px;\n            padding: 1.5rem;\n            margin-top: 2rem;\n            width: 100%;\n            max-width: 800px;\n            box-shadow: var(--shadow);\n            border-left: 5px solid var(--secondary);\n        }\n\n        .info-panel h3 {\n            font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;\n            color: var(--primary);\n            margin-top: 0;\n        }\n\n        .info-panel p {\n            line-height: 1.6;\n        }\n\n        footer {\n            margin-top: 4rem;\n            padding: 2rem 0;\n            width: 100%;\n            text-align: center;\n            background-color: var(--primary);\n            color: white;\n        }\n\n        .animation-controls {\n            display: flex;\n            gap: 1rem;\n            margin-bottom: 2rem;\n        }\n\n        @keyframes pulse {\n            0% { transform: scale(1); }\n            50% { transform: scale(1.05); }\n            100% { transform: scale(1); }\n        }\n\n        .pulse {\n            animation: pulse 2s infinite;\n        }\n    </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n    <header>\n        <h1>Binary Search Tree</h1>\n        <h2>A Visual Exploration of Ordered Data Structures</h2>\n    </header>\n\n    <div class=\"container\">\n        <div class=\"animation-controls\">\n            <button id=\"animateBtn\">Animate Search</button>\n            <button id=\"resetBtn\">Reset</button>\n        </div>\n\n        <div class=\"tree-container\" id=\"treeContainer\">\n            <!-- Tree will be rendered here -->\n        </div>\n\n        <div class=\"info-panel\">\n            <h3>About Binary Search Trees</h3>\n            <p>A Binary Search Tree (BST) is a node-based binary tree data structure where each node has at most two children referred to as the left child and the right child. For each node, all elements in the left subtree are less than the node's value, and all elements in the right subtree are greater than the node's value.</p>\n            <p>This visualization demonstrates the fundamental properties of BSTs through an elegant animated representation. Click \"Animate Search\" to see a demonstration of how searching works in a BST.</p>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <footer>\n        <p>© 2023 Visual Data Structures | Designed for Aesthetic Exploration</p>\n    </footer>\n\n    <script>\n        document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', function() {\n            // Sample BST data\n            const bstData = {\n                value: 50,\n                left: {\n                    value: 30,\n                    left: {\n                        value: 20,\n                        left: { value: 10 },\n                        right: { value: 25 }\n                    },\n                    right: {\n                        value: 40,\n                        left: { value: 35 },\n                        right: { value: 45 }\n                    }\n                },\n                right: {\n                    value: 70,\n                    left: {\n                        value: 60,\n                        left: { value: 55 },\n                        right: { value: 65 }\n                    },\n                    right: {\n                        value: 80,\n                        left: { value: 75 },\n                        right: { value: 90 }\n                    }\n                }\n            };\n\n            const container = document.getElementById('treeContainer');\n            const animateBtn = document.getElementById('animateBtn');\n            const resetBtn = document.getElementById('resetBtn');\n\n            let nodes = [];\n            let edges = [];\n            let animationInProgress = false;\n\n            // Initialize the tree\n            renderTree(bstData);\n\n            // Event listeners\n            animateBtn.addEventListener('click', function() {\n                if (!animationInProgress) {\n                    animateSearch(50);\n                }\n            });\n\n            resetBtn.addEventListener('click', function() {\n                if (!animationInProgress) {\n                    resetTree();\n                }\n            });\n\n            // Render the BST\n            function renderTree(tree) {\n                clearTree();\n                \n                // Calculate tree depth to determine spacing\n                const depth = getTreeDepth(tree);\n                const containerWidth = container.clientWidth;\n                const levelHeight = 100;\n                \n                // Start recursive rendering from root\n                renderNode(tree, containerWidth / 2, 50, containerWidth / 4, levelHeight, 1, depth);\n            }\n\n            // Recursive function to render nodes and edges\n            function renderNode(node, x, y, xOffset, yOffset, currentLevel, maxDepth) {\n                if (!node) return;\n\n                // Create node element\n                const nodeElement = document.createElement('div');\n                nodeElement.className = 'node';\n                nodeElement.textContent = node.value;\n                nodeElement.style.left = `${x - 30}px`;\n                nodeElement.style.top = `${y}px`;\n                container.appendChild(nodeElement);\n                \n                // Store node reference\n                nodes.push({\n                    element: nodeElement,\n                    value: node.value\n                });\n\n                // Calculate new xOffset based on current level\n                const dynamicXOffset = xOffset * (0.8 - (currentLevel / maxDepth) * 0.2);\n\n                // Render left child and edge\n                if (node.left) {\n                    const leftX = x - dynamicXOffset;\n                    const leftY = y + yOffset;\n                    \n                    // Create edge\n                    const edge = createEdge(x, y + 30, leftX, leftY - 30);\n                    container.appendChild(edge);\n                    edges.push(edge);\n                    \n                    // Render left child\n                    renderNode(node.left, leftX, leftY, dynamicXOffset / 2, yOffset, currentLevel + 1, maxDepth);\n                }\n\n                // Render right child and edge\n                if (node.right) {\n                    const rightX = x + dynamicXOffset;\n                    const rightY = y + yOffset;\n                    \n                    // Create edge\n                    const edge = createEdge(x, y + 30, rightX, rightY - 30);\n                    container.appendChild(edge);\n                    edges.push(edge);\n                    \n                    // Render right child\n                    renderNode(node.right, rightX, rightY, dynamicXOffset / 2, yOffset, currentLevel + 1, maxDepth);\n                }\n            }\n\n            // Create SVG edge between two points\n            function createEdge(x1, y1, x2, y2) {\n                const length = Math.sqrt(Math.pow(x2 - x1, 2) + Math.pow(y2 - y1, 2));\n                const angle = Math.atan2(y2 - y1, x2 - x1) * 180 / Math.PI;\n                \n                const edge = document.createElement('div');\n                edge.className = 'edge';\n                edge.style.width = `${length}px`;\n                edge.style.left = `${x1}px`;\n                edge.style.top = `${y1}px`;\n                edge.style.transform = `rotate(${angle}deg)`;\n                \n                return edge;\n            }\n\n            // Calculate tree depth\n            function getTreeDepth(node) {\n                if (!node) return 0;\n                return 1 + Math.max(getTreeDepth(node.left), getTreeDepth(node.right));\n            }\n\n            // Clear the tree\n            function clearTree() {\n                nodes.forEach(node => {\n                    node.element.remove();\n                });\n                edges.forEach(edge => {\n                    edge.remove();\n                });\n                nodes = [];\n                edges = [];\n            }\n\n            // Reset tree to initial state\n            function resetTree() {\n                nodes.forEach(node => {\n                    node.element.classList.remove('highlight');\n                    node.element.classList.remove('pulse');\n                });\n            }\n\n            // Animate BST search\n            function animateSearch(value) {\n                animationInProgress = true;\n                resetTree();\n                \n                // Find root node\n                const rootNode = nodes.find(node => node.value === bstData.value);\n                if (!rootNode) return;\n                \n                let currentNode = rootNode;\n                let delay = 0;\n                \n                // Highlight root node\n                setTimeout(() => {\n                    currentNode.element.classList.add('highlight');\n                    currentNode.element.classList.add('pulse');\n                }, delay);\n                \n                delay += 1500;\n                \n                // Perform search animation\n                function searchStep(nodeValue) {\n                    if (nodeValue === value) {\n                        // Found the value\n                        setTimeout(() => {\n                            const foundNode = nodes.find(n => n.value === nodeValue);\n                            if (foundNode) {\n                                foundNode.element.classList.add('highlight');\n                                foundNode.element.classList.add('pulse');\n                            }\n                            animationInProgress = false;\n                        }, delay);\n                        return;\n                    }\n                    \n                    // Move to next node\n                    setTimeout(() => {\n                        currentNode.element.classList.remove('highlight');\n                        currentNode.element.classList.remove('pulse');\n                        \n                        if (value < nodeValue) {\n                            // Go left\n                            const nextValue = currentNode.value === 50 ? 30 :\n                                            currentNode.value === 30 ? 20 :\n                                            currentNode.value === 20 ? 10 : null;\n                            if (nextValue) {\n                                currentNode = nodes.find(n => n.value === nextValue);\n                                currentNode.element.classList.add('highlight');\n                                currentNode.element.classList.add('pulse');\n                                delay += 1500;\n                                searchStep(nextValue);\n                            } else {\n                                animationInProgress = false;\n                            }\n                        } else {\n                            // Go right\n                            const nextValue = currentNode.value === 50 ? 70 :\n                                            currentNode.value === 70 ? 80 :\n                                            currentNode.value === 80 ? 90 : null;\n                            if (nextValue) {\n                                currentNode = nodes.find(n => n.value === nextValue);\n                                currentNode.element.classList.add('highlight');\n                                currentNode.element.classList.add('pulse');\n                                delay += 1500;\n                                searchStep(nextValue);\n                            } else {\n                                animationInProgress = false;\n                            }\n                        }\n                    }, delay);\n                }\n                \n                searchStep(currentNode.value);\n            }\n        });\n    </script>\n</body>\n</html>"
